Additionaly, Matiza is currently touring new road projects across the country following the release of funds by the Zimbabwe National Road Administration (Zinara) and also checked the  progress on the construction of Mutawatawa-Pfungwe Road. Zinara said it had released US $240m for road construction and maintenance to be disbursed to local authorities. This year’s allocation has increased by more than 40% compared to last year, release which was US $188m was released. Part of the funds will also be used to compensate individuals and companies whose properties lie along some of the proposed road expansion routes.  Moreover, Harare’s US $153m Robert Gabriel Mugabe (RGM) International Airport is also on schedule and will completed on time. The airport is expected to increase traffic, cargo volumes and passenger numbers.  